Operations Centre, in Poggio Renatico\n** Integrated Missile Air-defense Regiment (Rep. DAMI), in Poggio Renatico\n*** 11th Integrated Missile Air-defense Squadron, in Poggio Renatico \n*** 22nd Air Force Radar Squadron (GrRAM), in [[Licola (Pozzuoli)|Licola]], with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(V)]]\n*** 112th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Mortara, Lombardy|Mortara]], with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]]\n*** 113th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Lame di Concordia]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 114th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Potenza Picena]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 115th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Capo Mele]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 121st Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Poggio Ballone]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n*** 123rd Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Capo Frasca]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n*** 131st Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Jacotenente]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 132nd Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Isola di Capo Rizzuto|Capo Rizzuto]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 133rd Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[San Giovanni Teatino]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n*** 134th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Lampedusa]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 135th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Marsala]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 136th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Otranto]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 137th Remote Radar Station Flight, in [[Mezzogregorio]], with RAT-31DL\n\n=== Latvia ===\n{{Location map+ | Latvia | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Latvia | background = white |label='''[[Lielv\u0101rde Air Base|Lielv\u0101rde]]'''|lat= 56.778333 |long= 24.853333 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Latvia | background = white |label=<small></small>|lat= 56.778333 |long= 24.74 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Latvia | background = white |label=<small>[[Audri\u0146i]]</small>|lat= 56.583333 |long= 27.233333 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Latvia | background = white |label=<small>[[Ventspils|\u010calas]]</small>|lat= 57.357778 |long= 21.544167 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Latvian Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Latvian Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is located at [[Lielv\u0101rde Air Base]] and reports to the [[Baltic Air Surveillance Network]]'s Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre (RASCC) in [[Karm\u0117lava]], Lithuania, which in turn reports to CAOC Uedem.<ref>{{cite web|title=Latvia receives its first TPS-77 MRR air surveillance radar|url=http://www.mod.gov.lv/en/Aktualitates/Preses_pazinojumi/2018/03/08-02.aspx|publisher=Latvian Ministry of Defense|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n* '''Air Force Headquarters''', at [[Lielv\u0101rde Air Base]] \n** Air Surveillance Squadron, at Lielv\u0101rde Air Base\n*** Air Operations Centre, at Lielv\u0101rde Air Base\n*** 1st Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, at [[Lielv\u0101rde Air Base]], with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]]\n*** 2nd Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, in [[Audri\u0146i]], with AN/TPS-77(V)\n*** 3rd Radiotechnical (Radar) Post, in [[Ventspils|\u010calas]], with AN/TPS-77(V)\n*** Mobile Radar Section, with [[AN/TPS-77|TPS-77 MRR]]\n\n=== Lithuania ===\n{{Location map+ | Lithuania | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Lithuania | background = white |label='''[[Karm\u0117lava]]'''|lat= 54.972222 |long= 24.066667 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Lithuania | background = white |label=<small>[[Prienai|Antaver\u0161is]]</small>|lat= 54.633333 |long= 23.941667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Lithuania | background = white |label=<small>[[\u0160ilut\u0117|Degu\u010diai]]</small>|lat= 55.35 |long= 21.483333 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Lithuania | background = white |label=<small>[[Ignalina|Ceiki\u0161k\u0117s]]</small>|lat= 55.35 |long= 26.166667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Lithuanian Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Lithuanian Air Force]]'s Air Operations Control Centre is located in [[Karm\u0117lava]] and reports to the [[Baltic Air Surveillance Network]]'s Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre (RASCC) co-located in Karm\u0117lava, which in turn reports to CAOC Uedem.\n\n* '''Lithuanian Air Force Headquarters''', in [[Kaunas]]\n** [[Airspace Surveillance and Control Command (Lithuania)|Airspace Surveillance and Control Command]], in Kaunas\n*** Airspace Control Centre, in [[Karm\u0117lava]]\n*** 1st Radar Post, in [[Prienai|Antaver\u0161is]], with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]]\n*** 3rd Radar Post, in [[\u0160ilut\u0117|Degu\u010diai]], with AN/TPS-77(V)\n*** 4th Radar Post, in [[Ignalina|Ceiki\u0161k\u0117s]], with AN/TPS-77(V)\n\n=== Luxembourg ===\n[[Luxembourg]]'s airspace is monitored and guarded by the [[Belgian Air Component]]'s Control and Reporting Centre at [[Beauvechain Air Base]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nieuw Vluchtcontrolecentrum in Beauvechain|url=https://www.mil.be/nl/artikel/nieuw-vluchtcontrolecentrum-bevekom|publisher=Belgian Armed Forces|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Montenegro ===\nThe [[Armed Forces of Montenegro]] do not possess a modern air defense radar and the country's airspace is monitored by [[Italian Air Force]] radar sites. The Armed Forces Air Surveillance and Reporting Centre is located at [[Podgorica Airport]] in [[Golubovci]] and reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n in Spain.\n\n=== Netherlands ===\n{{Location map+ | Netherlands | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Netherlands | background = white |label='''[[Nieuw-Milligen]]'''|lat= 52.216667 |long= 5.783333 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Netherlands | background = white |label=|lat= 52.216667 |long= 5.73 |position=right|mark=Pink pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Netherlands | background = white |label=<small>[[Wier, Friesland|Wier]]</small>|lat= 53.251944 |long= 5.624167 |position=right|mark=Pink pog.svg}}\n|caption=Royal Netherlands Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Pink pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[SMART-L|SMART-L GB]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Royal Netherlands Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is located at [[Nieuw-Milligen]] and reports to CAOC Uedem. The air force's main radars are being replaced with two modern [[SMART-L|SMART-L GB]] radars.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''', in [[The Hague]]\n** Air Operations Control Station, in [[Nieuw-Milligen]]\n*** Control and Reporting Centre, in Nieuw-Milligen\n*** Radar Station South, in Nieuw-Milligen, with [[SMART-L|SMART-L GB]]\n*** Radar Station North, at [[Wier, Friesland|Wier]], with SMART-L GB\n\n=== Norway ===\n{{Location map+ | Norway | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label='''[[S\u00f8rreisa]]'''|lat= 69.072 |long= 17.965 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[Njunis]]</small>|lat= 68.75 |long= 19.5 |position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[Senja (island)|Senja]]</small>|lat= 69.333333 |long= 17.5 |position=top|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[Honningsv\u00e5g]]</small>|lat= 70.975833 |long= 25.983056 |position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[Vestv\u00e5g\u00f8y]]</small>|lat= 68.221389 |long= 13.784444 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[V\u00e5gs\u00f8y]]</small>|lat= 61.921111 |long= 5.193611 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Norway | background = white |label=<small>[[Eigersund|Skykula]]</small>|lat= 58.478333 |long= 6.063056 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n|caption=Royal Norwegian Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Yellow pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31SL|RAT-31SL/N]] <br/> [[File:Red ff0000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Hughes HR-3000|SINDRE I]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Royal Norwegian Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 3) in [[Reitan, Norway|Reitan]] was deactivated in 2008 and its responsibilities were transferred to the [[Combined Air Operations Centre Finderup]] (CAOC F). After CAOC F was deactivated in 2013 the responsibility for the air defense of Norway was transferred to CAOC Uedem in Germany and the Royal Norwegian Air Force's Control and Reporting Centre in S\u00f8rreisa reports to it. Until 2016 the Royal Norwegian Air Force's radar installations were distributed between two CRCs. That year the CRC M\u00e5ger\u00f8 was disbanded. In its place a wartime mobilization back-up CRC has been formed with a reduction in personnel from the around active 170 duty to about 50 [[Norwegian Home Guard|air force home guardsmen]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forsvaret.no/aktuelt/maageroe-takker-for-seg|title=Siste oppstilling p\u00e5 M\u00e5ger\u00f8|last=Forsvaret|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nb-NO}}</ref> The SINDRE I radars are a variant of the [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]] radar, which is also used in the German HADR radars. The newer [[Selex RAT-31SL|RAT-31SL/N]] radars are sometimes designated SINDRE II.\n\n* [[Norwegian Joint Headquarters|Armed Forces Operational Headquarters]], [[L\u00f8ding|Reitan]] near [[Bod\u00f8 Main Air Station]]\n** 131 Air Wing, in [[S\u00f8rreisa]]\n*** Control and Reporting Centre [[S\u00f8rreisa]]\n**** Radar Station [[Njunis]], with [[Selex RAT-31SL|RAT-31SL/N]]\n**** Radar Station [[Senja (island)|Senja]], with RAT-31SL/N\n**** Radar Station [[Honningsv\u00e5g]], with RAT-31SL/N\n**** Radar Station [[Vestv\u00e5g\u00f8y]], with [[Hughes HR-3000|SINDRE I]]\n**** Radar Station [[V\u00e5gs\u00f8y]], with SINDRE I\n**** Radar Station [[Eigersund|Skykula]], with SINDRE I\n\n=== Poland ===\n{{Location map+ | Poland | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label='''[[Pyry (neighborhood)|Pyry]]'''|lat= 52.133333 |long= 21.016667 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Gmina Sicienko|Os\u00f3wiec]]</small>|lat= 53.2 |long= 17.8 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[John Paul II International Airport Krak\u00f3w\u2013Balice|Krak\u00f3w-Balice]]</small>|lat= 50.086111 |long= 19.797222 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Wroc\u0142aw]]</small>|lat= 51.1 |long= 17.033333 |position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Sandomierz]]</small>|lat= 50.683333 |long= 21.75 |position=left|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[\u0141abunie]]</small>|lat= 50.666667 |long= 23.366667 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Lipowiec, Szczytno County|Lipowiec]]</small>|lat= 53.466667 |long= 21.133333 |position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Szypliszki]]</small>|lat= 54.25 |long= 23.066667 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Chru\u015bciel]]</small>|lat= 54.256667 |long= 19.811944 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Chojnice]]</small>|lat= 53.7 |long= 17.566667 |position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Poland | background = white |label=<small>[[Babki, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Babki]]</small>|lat= 52.316667 |long= 16.933333 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n|caption=Polish Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] <br/> [[File:Blue pog.svg|8px]] Radiotechnical Battalion <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Polish Air Force|Polish Armed Forces Operational Command]]'s Air Operations Centre is located in the Warsaw-[[Pyry (neighborhood)|Pyry]] neighborhood and reports to CAOC Uedem. The 3rd ''Wroc\u0142aw'' Radiotechnical Brigade is responsible for the operation of the armed forces' radar equipment and fields mainly obsolete [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]-era radars. As of 2018 the Polish Air Force possesses three modern [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] radars, which are listed below.\n\n* '''Armed Forces Operational Command''', in [[Warsaw]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Air Operations Center - Air Component Command |url=http://www.do.wp.mil.pl/info/cop/ |publisher=Polish Armed Forces |accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Structure |url=http://cop.wp.mil.pl/pl/3.html |publisher=Air Operations Centre - Air Component Command |accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref>\n** '''Air Operations Centre - Air Component Command''', in Warsaw-[[Pyry (neighborhood)|Pyry]]\n*** Mobile Air Operations Command Unit, in [[Babki, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Babki]]\n*** 22nd Command and Control Centre, in [[Gmina Sicienko|Os\u00f3wiec]]\n*** 32nd Command and Control Centre, at [[John Paul II International Airport Krak\u00f3w\u2013Balice|Krak\u00f3w-Balice Air Base]]\n*** 1st Air Operations Coordination Centre, in [[Gdynia]]\n*** 2nd Air Operations Coordination Centre, in [[Krakow]]\n*** 4th Air Operations Coordination Centre, in [[Szczecin]]\n*** 3rd ''Wroc\u0142aw'' Radiotechnical Brigade, in [[Wroc\u0142aw]]\n**** 3rd ''Sandomierz'' Radiotechnical Battalion, in [[Sandomierz]]\n***** 110th Long Range Radiolocating Post, in [[\u0141abunie]], with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]]\n**** 8th ''Szczeci\u0144'' Radiotechnical Battalion, in [[Lipowiec, Szczytno County|Lipowiec]]\n***** 184th Long Range Radiolocating Post, in [[Szypliszki]], with RAT-31DL\n***** 211th Long Range Radiolocating Post, in [[Chru\u015bciel]], with RAT-31DL\n**** 31st Radiotechnical Battalion, in Wroc\u0142aw\n**** 34th Radiotechnical Battalion, in [[Chojnice]]\n\n=== Portugal ===\n{{Location map+ | Portugal |AlternativeMap=Reliefkarte Portugal.png| relief = 1 | float=right | width=160| places=\n{{Location map~ | Portugal | background = white |label='''[[Monsanto Forest Park|Monsanto]]'''|lat= 38.719722 |long= -9.203056 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Portugal | background = white |label=<small>[[F\u00f3ia (mountain)|F\u00f3ia]]</small>|lat= 37.314795 |long= -8.596244 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Portugal | background = white |label=<small>Pilar</small>|lat= 41.266667 |long= -8.4 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Portugal | background = white |label=<small>[[Serra de Montejunto Protected Landscape|Montejunto]]</small>|lat= 39.175 |long= -9.05 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n|caption=Portuguese Air Force radar stations  (+ one station off map in [[Madeira]]) <br/> [[File:Red ff0000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Portuguese Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 10) in [[Lisbon]] was deactivated in 2013 and its responsibilities were transferred to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n in Spain.\n\n* '''Air Command''', in [[Lisbon]]\n** Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Monsanto Forest Park|Monsanto]]\n** Radar Station 1, on [[F\u00f3ia (mountain)|Monte F\u00f3ia]], with [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]]\n** Radar Station 2, on [[Monte Pilar]] in [[Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]], with HR-3000\n** Radar Station 3, at [[Serra de Montejunto Protected Landscape|Montejunto]], with HR-3000\n** Radar Station 4, on [[Pico do Arieiro]], on the island of [[Madeira]], with [[Indra Sistemas|LANZA 3-D]]\n\n=== Romania ===\n{{Location map+ | Romania | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label='''[[Bucharest]]'''|lat= 44.4325 |long= 26.103889 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[C\u00e2mpia Turzii]]</small>|lat= 46.533333 |long= 23.866667 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[Ovidiu]]</small>|lat= 44.27 |long= 28.56 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[Timi\u0219oara Traian Vuia International Airport|Giarmata]]</small>|lat= 45.833333 |long= 21.316667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[Suceava]]</small>|lat= 47.651389 |long= 26.255556 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[Craiova]]</small>|lat= 44.333333 |long= 23.816667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>[[Muntele Mare]]</small>|lat= 46.466667 |long= 23.2 |position=left|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Romania | background = white |label=<small>''[[B\u00e2rnova]]''</small>|lat= 47.15 |long= 27.583333 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Romanian Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(V)]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Romanian Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is headquartered in [[Bucharest]] and reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n. The radar station in B\u00e2rnova is officially designated and operated as a civilian radar station, however its data is fed into the military air surveillance system.\n\n* '''Air Operations Centre''', in [[Bucharest]]\n** 2nd Airspace Surveillance Centre \"North\", at [[RoAF 71st Air Base|71st Air Base]], in [[C\u00e2mpia Turzii]]\n** Radar Station, in [[Ovidiu]], with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(V)]]\n** Radar Station, at [[Timi\u0219oara Traian Vuia International Airport|Giarmata Airport]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n** Radar Station, in [[Suceava]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n** Radar Station, in [[Craiova]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n** Radar Station, on [[Muntele Mare]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n** Civil/Military Radar Station, in [[B\u00e2rnova]], with AN/FPS-117(V)\n\n=== Slovakia ===\nThe [[Slovak Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is located at [[Slia\u010d Air Base]] and reports to CAOC Uedem. The Slovak Air Force still operates obsolete [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]-era radars, which it intends to replace with fewer, but more capable Western 3-D radars as soon as possible. The future locations of the new radars are as of 2018 unknown.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''', at [[Slia\u010d Air Base]]\n** Command, Control and Surveillance Wing, at Slia\u010d Air Base\n*** Air Operations Centre, at Slia\u010d Air Base\n*** Radar Surveillance Battalion, in Slia\u010d Air Base\n\n=== Slovenia ===\n{{Location map+ | Slovenia | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Slovenia | background = white |label='''[[Zgornji Brnik|Brnik]]'''|lat= 46.239739 |long= 14.485853 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Slovenia | background = white |label=<small>[[Vrhnika]]</small>|lat= 45.962375 |long= 14.293736 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Slovenia | background = white |label=<small>[[Ho\u010dko Pohorje]]</small>|lat= 46.500347 |long= 15.570408 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n|caption=Slovenian Air Force and Air Defense radar stations <br/> [[File:Purple pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Ground Master 400|GM 403]] <br /> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Slovenian Air Force and Air Defence|Slovenian Air Force and Air Defense]]'s Airspace Surveillance and Control Centre is headquartered in [[Zgornji Brnik|Brnik]] and reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n.\n\nThe [[Italian Air Force]]'s 4th Wing at [[Grosseto Air Base]] and 36th Wing at [[Gioia del Colle Air Base]] rotate a [[Quick Reaction Alert|QRA]] flight of [[Eurofighter Typhoon]]s to [[Istrana Air Base]], which are responsible for the air defense of Northern Italy and Slovenia.\n\n* '''Forces Command''', in [[Vrhnika]]\n** 15th Military Aviation Regiment, at [[Cerklje ob Krki Air Base]]\n*** 16th Airspace Surveillance and Control Battalion in [[Zgornji Brnik|Brnik]]\n**** Airspace Surveillance and Control Centre, in Brnik\n**** 1st Radar Station, in [[Vrhnika]], with [[Ground Master 403|GM 403]]\n**** 2nd Radar Station, in [[Ho\u010dko Pohorje]], with GM 403\n\n=== Spain ===\n{{Location map+ | Spain | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[El Frasno]]</small>|lat=41.41388|long=-1.495016|position=left|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Villatobas]]</small>|lat=39.9|long=-3.333333|position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Constantina, Seville|Constantina]]</small>|lat=37.866667|long=-5.616667|position=right|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Roses, Girona|Roses]]</small>|lat=42.263056|long=3.183056|position=right|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Aitana]]</small>|lat=38.660833|long=-0.274722|position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Puig Major]]</small>|lat=39.8|long=2.8|position=right|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Motril]]</small>|lat=36.75|long=-3.516667|position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[A Barbanza|Barbanza]]</small>|lat=42.613889|long=-8.906667|position=right|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Alcal\u00e1 de los Gazules]]</small>|lat=36.466667|long=-5.716667|position=left|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Espinosa de los Monteros]]</small>|lat=43.066667|long=-3.533333|position=right|mark=Yellow pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>Sierra Espu\u00f1a</small>|lat=37.771002|long=-1.500162|position=right|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label='''[[Torrej\u00f3n Air Base|Torrej\u00f3n]]'''|lat=40.496667|long=-3.445833|position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Spain | background = white |label=<small>[[Zaragoza Air Base|Zaragoza]]</small>|lat=41.666111|long=-1.041667|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n|caption=Spanish Air Force radar stations (+ two stations off map in the [[Canary Islands]]) <br/> [[File:Black pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Indra Sistemas|LANZA 3-D]] <br/>[[File:Yellow pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31SL|RAT-31SL/T]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Spanish Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 8) at [[Torrej\u00f3n Air Base]] was deactivated in 2013 and replaced at same location by CAOC Torrejon, which took over the functions of CAOC 5, CAOC 7, CAOC 8 and CAOC 10. CAOC Torrej\u00f3n is responsible for the NATO airspace South of the Alps.\n\n* '''Combat Air Command''', at [[Torrej\u00f3n Air Base]]\n** Combat Air Command Headquarter (CGMACOM), at Torrej\u00f3n Air Base\n*** Air Operations Centre / NATO CAOC Torrej\u00f3n\n** Command and Control Systems Headquarter (JSMC), at Torrej\u00f3n Air Base\n*** Central Command and Control Group (GRUCEMAC), at Torrej\u00f3n Air Base\n*** Northern Command and Control Group 