ht|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[K\u00f6rfez, Kocaeli|K\u00f6rfez]]</small>|lat= 40.783333 |long= 29.733333 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[\u0130zmir|Karabelen]]</small>|lat= 38.42 |long= 27.14 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[\u00c7anakkale]]</small>|lat= 40.155833 |long= 26.413611 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[Erzurum]]</small>|lat= 39.908611 |long= 41.276944 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[Dat\u00e7a]]</small>|lat= 36.7283 |long= 27.6869 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[Inebolu]]</small>|lat=41.95|long= 34.583333 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[\u0130skenderun]]</small>|lat= 36.5817 |long= 36.165 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Turkey | background = white |label=<small>[[Rize]]</small>|lat= 41.024722 |long= 40.522222 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n|caption=Turkish Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Turkish Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 6) in [[Eskisehir]] was deactivated in 2013 and its responsibilities were transferred to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n in Spain. Turkey's Air Force fields a mix of [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]], [[AN/FPS-117]], [[Selex RAT-31SL|RAT-31SL]] and [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] radars, however the exact number of each of these radar and their location in the Turkish radar system is unknown.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''' (COA), in \n** Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Ankara|Ahlatl\u0131bel]]\n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[Ankara|Ahlatl\u0131bel]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[K\u00f6rfez, Kocaeli|K\u00f6rfez]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[\u0130zmir|Karabelen]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[\u00c7anakkale]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[Erzurum]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[Dat\u00e7a]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[\u0130nebolu]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[\u0130skenderun]], with \n*** Aerial Surveillance Radar Post, in [[Rize]], with\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\n{{Location map+ | United Kingdom | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label='''[[RAF Boulmer|Boulmer]]'''|lat= 55.421944 |long= -1.603333 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label='''[[RAF Scampton|Scampton]]'''|lat= 53.307778 |long= -0.550833 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Benbecula|Benbecula]]</small>|lat= 57.617222 |long= -7.446111 |position=left|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Buchan|Buchan]]</small>|lat= 57.458333 |long= -1.811944 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Saxa Vord|Saxa Vord]]</small>|lat= 60.8275 |long= -0.841111 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Trimingham|Trimingham]]</small>|lat= 52.892778 |long= 1.400556 |position=left|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Portreath|Portreath]]</small>|lat= 50.271389 |long= -5.263333 |position=left|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Staxton Wold|Staxton Wold]]</small>|lat= 54.186389 |long= -0.434444 |position=left|mark=Black pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom | background = white |label=<small>[[RRH Brizlee Wood|Brizlee Wood]]</small>|lat= 55.41831 |long= -1.76844  |position=left|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Royal Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/FPS-117]] or [[AN/TPS-77]] <br/> [[File:Blue pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[BAE Systems|AR-327]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Royal Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 9) at [[RAF High Wycombe]] was deactivated in 2008 and its responsibilities were transferred to the [[Combined Air Operations Centre Finderup]] (CAOC F). After CAOC F was deactivated in 2013 the responsibility for the air defense of the United Kingdom was transferred to CAOC Uedem in Germany. The Royal Air Force's Control and Reporting Centres report to it.\n\n* '''[[No. 1 Group RAF]]''', at [[RAF High Wycombe]]\n** [[UK Air Surveillance and Control Systems]], at [[RAF Boulmer]]\n*** Control and Reporting Centre, at RAF Boulmer\n*** [[No 1 Air Control Centre|No. 1 Air Control Centre]], at [[RAF Scampton]] (National Air Control Centre)\n*** [[RRH Benbecula]], in [[North Uist]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]\n*** [[RRH Brizlee Wood]], in [[Eglingham|Shipley]], with [[AN/FPS-117]]\n*** [[RRH Buchan]], in [[Boddam, Aberdeenshire|Boddam]], with AN/TPS-77\n*** [[RRH Portreath]], in [[Portreath]], with [[BAE Systems|AR-327]]\n*** [[RRH Saxa Vord]], in [[Unst]], with AN/TPS-77\n*** [[RRH Trimingham]], in [[Trimingham]], with AN/FPS-117 (satellite station of [[RRH Neatishead]])\n*** [[RRH Staxton Wold]], in [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]], had an AN/TPS-77 radar, which was moved to RRH Saxa Vord in 2017, future plans for RRH Staxton Wold are as of 2018 unknown.\n\n=== United States ===\nThe [[United States Air Force]]'s control centres and radar stations are part of the [[Canada|Canadian]]/American [[North American Aerospace Defense Command]].\n\n== Non-NATO European air defense systems ==\n=== Austria ===\n{{Location map+ | Austria | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Austria | background = white |label='''[[St Johann im Pongau|Basisraum]]'''|lat= 47.320556 |long= 13.186667 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Austria | background = white |label=<small>Kolomansberg\n</small>|lat= 47.87738 |long= 13.27526 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Austria | background = white |label=<small> Steinmandl </small>|lat= 48.575278 |long= 16.396111 |position=left|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Austria | background = white |label=<small> Speikkogel</small>|lat= 46.786667 |long= 14.971667 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n|caption=Austrian Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar Station with [[Selex RAT-31DL]] <br> \n [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Center ''\"Basisraum\"''}}\n\n* '''[[Austrian Air Force]]''' - [[GOLDHAUBE]] system:\n** Command and Control Center ''\"Basisraum\"'', in [[St Johann im Pongau]]\n*** [[Kolomansberg]] Radar Station\n*** [[Gro\u00dfer Speikkogel]] Radar Station\n*** [[Steinmandl]] Radar Station\n\n=== Switzerland ===\n{{Location map+ | Switzerland | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Switzerland | background = white |label='''[[D\u00fcbendorf Air Base|D\u00fcbendorf]]'''|lat= 47.398611 |long= 8.648056 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Switzerland | background = white |label=<small>[[Pilatus (mountain)|Pilatus]]</small>|lat= 46.973889 |long= 8.241111 |position=left|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Switzerland | background = white |label=<small>[[Scopi]]</small>|lat= 46.571667 |long= 8.83 |position=left|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Switzerland | background = white |label=<small>[[Weisshorn (Bernese Alps)|Weisshorn]]</small>|lat= 46.38382 |long= 7.473604 |position=left|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Switzerland | background = white |label=<small>[[Weissfluh]]</small>|lat= 46.835167 |long= 9.794389 |position=left|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n|caption=Swiss Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\n* '''[[Swiss Air Force]]''' - [[FLORAKO]] system:\n** Air Defence & Direction Center, at [[D\u00fcbendorf Air Base]]\n*** [[Mount Pilatus|Pilatus]] Radar Station\n*** [[Scopi]] Radar Station\n*** [[Weisshorn (Bernese Alps)|Weisshorn]] Radar Station\n*** [[Weissfluh]] Radar Station\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Military installations of NATO]]\n[[Category:Air defence radar networks]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Patriot System 2.jpg|thumb|300px |A Patriot system of the [[German Air Force]] in August 2005.]]\nThe '''NATO Integrated Air Defense System''' (short: '''NATINADS''') is a [[command and control]] network combining radars and other facilities spread throughout the [[NATO]] alliance's [[air defence]] forces. It formed in the mid-1950s and became operational in 1962 as '''NADGE'''. It has been constantly upgraded since its formation, notably with the integration of [[Airborne Early Warning]] aircraft in the 1970s. The [[United Kingdom]] maintained its own network, but was fully integrated with the network since the introduction of the [[Linesman/Mediator]] network in the 1970s. Similarly, the German network maintained an independent nature through '''GEADGE'''.\n\n== Development ==\nDevelopment was approved by the NATO Military Committee in December 1955. The system was to be based on four air defense regions (ADRs) coordinated by [[Supreme Allied Commander|SACEUR]] (Supreme Allied Commander Europe). Starting from 1956 early warning coverage was extended across [[Western Europe]] using 18 radar stations. This part of the system was completed by 1962. Linked to existing national radar sites the coordinated system was called the '''NATO Air Defence Ground Environment''' ('''NADGE''').\n\nFrom 1960 NATO countries agreed to place all their air defence forces under the command of SACEUR in the event of war. These forces included command & control (C2) systems, radar installations, and Surface-to-Air (SAM) missile units as well as interceptor aircraft.\n\nBy 1972 NADGE was converted into NATINADS consisting of 84 radar sites and associated Control Reporting Centers (CRC) and in the 1980s the '''Airborne Early Warning / Ground Environment Integration Segment (AEGIS)''' upgraded the NATINADS with the possibility to integrate the AWACS radar picture and all of its information into its visual displays. (NOTE: This AEGIS is not to be confused with the U.S.Navy [[Aegis Combat System|AEGIS]], a shipboard fire control radar and weapons system.) AEGIS processed the information through Hughes H5118ME computers, which replaced the H3118M computers installed at NADGE sites in the late 1960s and early 1970s.\n\nNATINADS ability to handle data increased with faster clock rates. The H5118M computer had a staggering 1 megabyte of memory and could handle 1.2 million instructions per second while the former model had a memory of only 256 kilobytes and a clock speed of 150,000 instructions per seconds.<ref>http://ed-thelen.org/aadcp.html</ref>\n\nNATINADS/AEGIS were complemented, in West Germany by the '''German Air Defence Ground Environment (GEADGE)''', an updated radar network adding the southern part of Germany to the European system and '''Coastal Radar Integration System (CRIS)''', adding data links from Danish coastal radars.\n\nIn order to counter the hardware obsolescence, during the mid-90's NATO started the '''AEGIS Site Emulator (ASE)''' program allowing the NATINADS/AEGIS sites to replace the proprietary hardware (the 5118ME computer and the various operator consoles IDM-2, HMD-22, IDM-80) with commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) servers and workstations.\n\nIn the first years 2000, the initial ASE capability was expanded with the possibility to run, thanks to the new hardware power, multiple site emulators on the same hardware, so the system was renamed into '''Multi-AEGIS Site Emulator (MASE)'''. The NATO system designed to replace MASE in the near future is the [[Air Command and Control System]] (ACCS).\n\nBecause of changing politics, NATO expanding and financial crises most European (NATO) countries are trying to cut defence budgets; as a direct result, lots of obsolete and outdated NATINADS facilities are phased out earlier. Currently (2013) still operational NATO radar sites in Europe are these:\n\n== Allied Air Command ==\n'''[[Allied Air Command]]''' (AIRCOM) is the [[Staff (military)|central command]] of all [[NATO]] [[air force]]s on the European continent. The command is based at [[Ramstein Air Base]] in [[Germany]] and has two subordinate commands in Germany and Spain. The [[Royal Canadian Air Force]] and [[United States Air Force]] fall under command of the [[Canada|Canadian]]/American [[North American Aerospace Defense Command]].\n\n* '''[[Allied Air Command]]''', at [[Ramstein Air Base]], Germany\n** '''CAOC Torrej\u00f3n''', at [[Torrej\u00f3n Air Base]], Spain - responsible for the airspace South of the [[Alps]]\n*** Albania: Air Surveillance Centre, at [[Tirana International Airport N\u00ebn\u00eb Tereza|Tirana International Airport]]\n*** Bulgaria: Air Sovereignty Operations Centre, in [[Sofia]] \n*** Croatia: Airspace Surveillance Centre, in [[Podvornica]]\n*** Greece: Air Operations Centre, at [[Larissa Air Base]]\n*** Italy: Air Operations Centre, in [[Poggio Renatico]]\n*** Montenegro: Air Surveillance and Reporting Centre, at [[Podgorica Airport]]\n*** Portugal: Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Monsanto Forest Park|Monsanto]]\n*** Romania: Air Operations Center, in [[Bucharest]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.roaf.ro/?p=3868|title=AOC {{!}} Fortele Aeriene Romane|website=www.roaf.ro|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-28}}</ref> \n*** Slovenia: Airspace Surveillance and Control Centre, in [[Zgornji Brnik|Brnik]]\n*** Spain: Air Operations Centre, in Torrej\u00f3n\n**** Central Command and Control Group, at Torrej\u00f3n Air Base\n**** Northern Command and Control Group, at [[Zaragoza Air Base]]\n*** Turkey: Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Ankara|Ahlatl\u0131bel]]\n** '''CAOC Uedem''', in Uedem, Germany - responsible for the airspace North of the [[Alps]]\n*** [[Baltic Air Surveillance Network]] - Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre, in [[Karm\u0117lava]]\n**** Estonia: Air Operations Control Centre, at [[\u00c4mari Air Base]]\n**** Latvia: Air Operations Centre, at [[Lielv\u0101rde Air Base]]\n**** Lithuania: Airspace Control Centre, in [[Karm\u0117lava]]\n*** Belgium: Control and Reporting Centre, at [[Beauvechain Air Base]]\n*** Czech Republic: Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Hlavenec]]\n*** Denmark: Control and Reporting Centre, at [[Karup Air Base]]\n*** Germany: Air Operations Centre, in Uedem\n**** Control and Reporting Centre 2, in [[Erndtebr\u00fcck]]\n**** Control and Reporting Centre 3, in [[Sch\u00f6newalde]]\n*** Hungary: Air Operations Centre, in [[Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n*** Iceland: Control and Reporting Centre, at [[Keflavik Air Base]]\n*** Luxembourg: airspace controlled by Belgium's Control and Reporting Centre, at [[Beauvechain Air Base]]\n*** Netherlands: Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Nieuw-Milligen]]\n*** Norway: Control and Reporting Centre, in [[S\u00f8rreisa]]\n*** Poland: Air Operations Centre, in Warsaw-[[Pyry (neighborhood)|Pyry]]\n**** 22nd Command and Control Centre, in [[Gmina Sicienko|Os\u00f3wiec]]\n**** 32nd Command and Control Centre, in [[Balice, Lesser Poland Voivodeship|Balice]]\n*** Slovakia: Air Operations Centre, at [[Slia\u010d Air Base]]\n*** United Kingdom: Control and Reporting Centre, at [[RAF Boulmer]]\n\n== Radar stations ==\n=== Albania ===\nThe [[Albanian Air Force]] does not possess any fixed radar installations. Its air space is monitored by [[Italian Air Force]] and [[Greek Air Force]] radars. The [[Albanian Air Force]]'s Air Surveillance Centre at [[Tirana International Airport N\u00ebn\u00eb Tereza|Tirana International Airport]] reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n in Spain, while the Italian Air Force's 36th Wing at [[Gioia del Colle Air Base]] is responsible for the air defense of [[Albania]]. Albania is buying two mobile [[Lockheed Martin]] [[AN/TPS-77]] radars to provide its Armed Forces with its own radar capability.\n\n=== Belgium ===\nThe [[Belgian Air Component]]'s Control and Reporting Centre was based at [[Glons]], where also its main radar was located. The radar was deactivated in 2015<ref>{{cite web|title=Glons Verliest zijn Koepel, niet zijn Zicht|url=https://www.mil.be/nl/artikel/glons-verliest-zijn-koepel-niet-zijn-zicht|publisher=Belgian Armed Forces|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref> and the Centre moved to [[Beauvechain Air Base]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nieuw Vluchtcontrolecentrum in Beauvechain|url=https://www.mil.be/nl/artikel/nieuw-vluchtcontrolecentrum-bevekom|publisher=Belgian Armed Forces|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref> The Belgian Control and Reporting Centre reports to CAOC Uedem in Germany and is also responsible for guarding the airspace of [[Luxembourg]]. At the new location the Control and Reporting Centre uses digital radar data of the civilian radars of [[Belgocontrol]] and the [[Marconi|Marconi S-723]] radar of the Air Component's Air Traffic Control Centre in [[Semmerzake]].\n\n=== Bulgaria ===\nThe [[Bulgarian Air Force]]'s Air Sovereignty Operations Centre is located in [[Sofia]] and reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n. The Bulgarian Air Force fields three control and surveillance zones, which operate obsolete [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]-era radars. The Bulgarian Air Force intends to replace these radars with fewer, but more capable Western 3-D radars as soon as possible. The future locations of the new radars are as of 2018 unknown.\n\n* '''Joint Forces Command''', in [[Sofia]]\n** Air Sovereignty Operational Center (ASOC), in Sofia \n*** Base Operative Center (part of 3rd Air Base), [[Graf Ignatievo Air Base]], operational control of fighter aviation\n*** Command, Control and Surveillance Base, in Sofia\n**** 1st Control and Surveillance Zone, in [[Bozhurishte]], [[Sofia Province]]\n**** 2nd Control and Surveillance Zone, in [[Trud, Bulgaria|Trud]], [[Plovdiv Province]]\n**** 3rd Control and Surveillance Zone, in [[Bratovo, Burgas Province|Bratovo]], [[Burgas Province]]\n\n=== Canada ===\nThe [[Royal Canadian Air Force]]'s control centres and radar stations are part of the [[Canada|Canadian]]/American [[North American Aerospace Defense Command]].\n\n=== Croatia ===\n{{Location map+ | Croatia |AlternativeMap=Croatia relief map.png| relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label='''[[Podvornica]]'''|lat= 45.616667 |long= 16.066667 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label=<small>[[Medvednica|Mount Sljeme]]</small>|lat= 45.916667 |long= 15.966667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label=<small>[[Borinci]]</small>|lat= 45.316667 |long= 18.733333 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label=<small>[[Papuk]]</small>|lat= 45.533333 |long= 17.65|position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label=<small>[[U\u010dka]]</small>|lat= 45.285 |long= 14.201944 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Croatia | background = white |label=<small>[[Pelje\u0161ac|Mount Rota]]</small>|lat= 42.966667 |long= 17.366667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Croatian Air Force and Air Defense radar stations<br/>[[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(E)1T]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Croatian Air Force and Air Defense]]'s Airspace Surveillance Centre is headquartered in [[Podvornica]] and reports to CAOC Torrej\u00f3n.\n\n* '''Air Force and Air Defense Command'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scramblemagazine.nl/orbats/croatia |title=Orbats - Scramble |website=Scramblemagazine.nl |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>\n** Airspace Surveillance and Control Battalion, at [[91st Air Force Base]] ([[Zagreb]] - Pleso)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.osrh.hr/#rubData/HTML/HR/O%20NAMA/HRZ/02_20180226_Bojna_zra%C4%8Dnog_motrenja_i_navo%C4%91enja/Bojna_zra%C4%8Dnog_motrenja_i_navo%C4%91enja_HR.htm|title=OSRH - Glavna|last=Krizmani\u0107|first=Goran|website=www.osrh.hr|language=hr|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref>\n*** Airspace Surveillance Centre, in [[Podvornica]]\n*** Sector Operational Centre, in [[Split, Croatia|Split]]\n*** [[Medvednica|Mount Sljeme]] Radar Post, with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(E)1T]]\n*** [[Borinci]] Radar Post, with AN/FPS-117(E)1T\n*** [[Papuk]] Radar Post, with AN/FPS-117(E)1T\n*** [[U\u010dka]] Radar Post, with AN/FPS-117(E)1T\n*** [[Pelje\u0161ac|Mount Rota]], with AN/FPS-117(E)1T\n\n=== Czech Republic ===\n{{Location map+ | Czech Republic | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Czech Republic | background = white |label='''[[Hlavenec]]'''|lat= 50.233333 |long= 14.7 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Czech Republic | background = white |label=<small>[[Nepolisy]]</small>|lat= 50.182685 |long= 15.465868 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Czech Republic | background = white |label=<small>[[Sokolnice]]</small>|lat= 49.118982 |long= 16.762345 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Czech Republic | background = white |label=<small>[[\u010ceradice|V\u011btru\u0161ice]]</small>|lat= 50.299722 |long= 13.473333 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n|caption=Czech Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Czech Air Force]]'s Control and Reporting Centre is located in [[Hlavenec]] and reports to CAOC Uedem.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''', in [[Prague]]\n** 26th Air Command, Control and Surveillance Regiment, in [[Star\u00e1 Boleslav]]\n*** 261st [[Control and Reporting Centre]] (CRC), in [[Hlavenec]]\n*** 262nd Radiotechnical Battalion, in Hlavenec\n**** 1st Radiotechnical Company, in [[Nepolisy]], with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]]\n**** 4th Radiotechnical Company, in [[Sokolnice]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 263nd Support Battalion, in [[Hlavenec]]\n**** Reserve Control and Reporting Centre, in [[\u010ceradice|V\u011btru\u0161ice]]\n\n=== Denmark ===\n{{Location map+ | Denmark | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Denmark | background = white |label='''[[Karup Air Base|Karup]]'''|lat= 56.2975 |long= 9.124722 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Denmark | background = white |label=<small>[[Skagen]]</small>|lat= 57.722222 |long= 10.587778 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Denmark | background = white |label=<small>[[Skrydstrup Air Base|Skrydstrup]]</small>|lat= 55.233333 |long= 9.266667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Denmark | background = white |label=<small>[[Almindingen|Bornholm]]</small>|lat= 55.124 |long= 14.925 |position=left|mark=Brown 804000 pog.svg}}\n|caption=Royal Danish Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/TPS-77]]  <br/> [[File:Brown 804000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Marconi|Marconi S-723]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Royal Danish Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 1) in [[Finderup]] was deactivated in 2008 and replaced at the same location by the [[Combined Air Operations Centre Finderup]] (CAOC F), which had responsibility for the airspaces of [[Iceland]], [[Norway]], [[Denmark]] and the [[United Kingdom]]. CAOC F was deactivated in 2013 and its responsibilities were transferred to CAOC Uedem in Germany. The national Danish Control and Reporting Centre is located at [[Karup Air Base]] and it reports to CAOC Uedem.\n\nThe [[Thule Air Base]] in [[Greenland]] is a [[United States Air Force]] installation and its radars are part of the [[North American Aerospace Defense Command]].\n\n* '''Air Force Tactical Command''', at [[Karup Air Base]]\n** Air Control Wing, at Karup Air Base\n*** Control and Reporting Centre, at Karup Air Base\n*** Radar Station Skagen, in [[Skagen]], with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]]\n*** Radar Station Skrydstrup, at [[Skrydstrup Air Base]], with [[AN/TPS-77]]\n*** Radar Station [[Bornholm]], in [[Almindingen]], with [[Marconi|Marconi S-723]]\n\n=== Estonia ===\n{{Location map+ | Estonia | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Estonia | background = white |label='''[[\u00c4mari Air Base|\u00c4mari]]'''|lat= 59.262222 |long= 24.218611 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Estonia | background = white |label=<small>[[Leval\u00f5pme]]</small>|lat= 58.616667 |long= 23.25 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Estonia | background = white |label=<small>[[Otep\u00e4\u00e4]]</small>|lat= 58.05 |long= 26.5 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Estonia | background = white |label=<small>[[Kellavere]]</small>|lat= 59.078889 |long= 26.530556 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Estonian Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Purple pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Ground Master 400|GM 403]] <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Estonian Air Force]]'s Air Operations Control Centre is located at [[\u00c4mari Air Base]] and reports to the [[Baltic Air Surveillance Network]]'s Regional Airspace Surveillance Coordination Centre (RASCC) in [[Karm\u0117lava]], Lithuania, which in turn reports to CAOC Uedem.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''', in [[Tallinn]]\n** [[Air Surveillance Wing (Estonia)|Air Surveillance Wing]], at [[\u00c4mari Air Base]] \n*** Air Operations Control Centre, at \u00c4mari Air Base\n*** Engineering and Technical Group, at \u00c4mari Air Base\n**** Radar Station, in [[Leval\u00f5pme]], with [[Ground Master 403|GM 403]]\n**** Radar Station, in [[Otep\u00e4\u00e4]], with GM 403\n**** Radar Station, in [[Kellavere]], with [[AN/TPS-77|AN/TPS-77(V)]]\n**** Airport Surveillance Radar at [[\u00c4mari Air Base]], with [[Airport Surveillance Radar|ASR-8]]\n\n=== France ===\n{{Location map+ | France | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | France | background = white |label='''[[Lyon \u2013 Mont Verdun Air Base|Mont Verdun]]'''|lat= 45.85 |long= 4.783333 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | France | background = white |label=<small>[[Mont-de-Marsan Air Base|Mont-de-Marsan]]</small>|lat= 43.911667 |long= -0.509167 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | France | background = white |label=<small>[[Cinq-Mars-la-Pile]]</small>|lat= 47.3483 |long= 0.4625 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | France | background = white |label=|lat= 45.85 |long= 4.97 |position=left|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | France | background = white |label=<small>[[Mont Agel]]</small>|lat= 43.775278 |long= 7.426389 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n|caption=French Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Purple pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Ground Master 400|GM 406]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[French Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is located at [[Lyon \u2013 Mont Verdun Air Base|Mont Verdun Air Base]] and reports to CAOC Uedem. Most French radar sites use the PALMIER radar, which is being taken out of service. By 2022 all PALMIER radars will have been replaced with new radar stations using the [[Ground Master 400|GM 403]] radar.\n\n* '''Air Defense and Air Operations Command'''\n** Air Operations Brigade, at [[Lyon \u2013 Mont Verdun Air Base|Mont Verdun Air Base]]\n*** Air Operations Centre, at Mont Verdun Air Base\n*** Control and Reporting Centre, at [[Mont-de-Marsan Air Base]]\n*** Control and Reporting Centre, in [[Cinq-Mars-la-Pile]]\n*** Mont Verdun Air Base radar, with GM [[Ground Master 400|GM 406]]\n*** \u00c9l\u00e9ment Air Rattach\u00e9 (EAR) 943, on [[Mont Agel]], with GM 406\n\nAdditionally the French Air Force fields a GM 406 radar at the [[Cayenne \u2013 F\u00e9lix Ebou\u00e9 Airport|Cayenne-Rochambeau Air Base]] in [[French Guiana]] to protect the [[Guiana Space Centre]] in [[Kourou]].\n\n=== Germany ===\n{{Location map+ | Germany | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Putgarten]]</small>|lat= 54.673333 |long= 13.4175 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[C\u00f6lpin]]</small>|lat=53.5|long= 13.416667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Berlin Tempelhof Airport|Tempelhof]]</small>|lat= 52.473611 |long= 13.401667 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Kalkhorst|Elmenhorst]]</small>|lat= 53.970278 |long= 11.045833 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[D\u00f6bern]]</small>|lat= 51.616667 |long=14.6|position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Gleina]]</small>|lat= 51.266667 |long= 11.733056 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[D\u00f6braberg]]</small>|lat= 50.266667 |long= 11.65 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Gro\u00dfer Arber]]</small>|lat= 49.112222 |long=13.134444|position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=|lat=50.988889|long=8.2|position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Me\u00dfstetten]]</small>|lat= 48.180556 |long= 8.9625 |position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Freising]]</small>|lat= 48.402778 |long= 11.748889 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Lauda-K\u00f6nigshofen|Lauda]]</small>|lat= 49.568611 |long= 9.703889 |position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Erbeskopf]]</small>|lat= 49.730444 |long=7.090639|position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Brekendorf]]</small>|lat=54.416667|long=9.633333|position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Brockzetel]]</small>|lat=53.484444|long=7.640833|position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Visselh\u00f6vede]]</small>|lat=52.966667|long=9.583333|position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Brakel, Germany|Auenhausen]]</small>|lat=51.716667|long=9.183333|position=right|mark=Purple pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Marienbaum]]</small>|lat=51.698056|long=6.375556|position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Erndtebr\u00fcck]]</small>|lat=50.988889|long=8.3|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label=<small>[[Sch\u00f6newalde]]</small>|lat=51.8125|long=13.222778|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Germany | background = white |label='''[[Uedem]]'''|lat= 51.6675 |long= 6.275 |position=bottom|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n|caption=German Air Force radar stations <br/> [[File:Red ff0000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Hughes HR-3000|HADR]] <br/> [[File:Purple pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Ground Master 400|GM 406F]] <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/FPS-117|RRP-117]] <br /> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[German Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 2) in [[Uedem]] was deactivated in 2008 and reactivated as CAOC Uedem in 2013. CAOC Uedem is responsible for the NATO airspace North of the Alps. The HADR radars are a variant of the [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]] radar, while the RRP-117 radars are a variant of the [[AN/FPS-117]].\n\n* '''Air Operations Centre''' (Zentrum Luftoperationen der Luftwaffe) (NATO CAOC Uedem), in [[Uedem]]\n** Control and Reporting Centre 2 (Einsatzf\u00fchrungsbereich 2), in [[Erndtebr\u00fcck]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Einsatzf\u00fchrungsbereich 2|url=http://www.luftwaffe.de/portal/a/luftwaffe/start/org/ruelog/efb2/!ut/p/z1/04_Sj9CPykssy0xPLMnMz0vMAfIjo8zinSx8QnyMLI2MfMIsXQw8DX29TS0tnYyCQsz0wwkpiAJKG-AAjgb6wSmp-pFAM8xxmOFo4m2qH6wfpR-VlViWWKFXkF9UkpNaopeYDHKhfmRGYl5KTmpAfrIjRKAgN6LcoNxREQD7-Mlf/dz/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/#Z7_B8LTL2922LV9D0I1MK599BA4K5|publisher=German Air Force|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref>\n*** Operations Squadron 21, in Erndtebr\u00fcck\n*** Operations Support Squadron 22, in Erndtebr\u00fcck\n**** Sensor Platoon I, in [[Lauda-K\u00f6nigshofen|Lauda]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 240 \"Loneship\", in Erndtebr\u00fcck with [[Ground Master 400|GM 406F]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 246 \"Hardwheel\", on [[Erbeskopf]] with [[Hughes HR-3000|HADR]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 247 \"Batman\", in Lauda with GM 406F\n***** Remote Radar Post 248 \"Coldtrack\", in [[Freising]] with GM 406F\n***** Remote Radar Post 249 \"Sweet Apple\", in [[Me\u00dfstetten]] with HADR\n**** Sensor Platoon II, in [[Brakel, Germany|Auenhausen]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 241 \"Crabtree\", in [[Marienbaum]] with HADR\n***** Remote Radar Post 242 \"Backwash\", in [[Brakel, Germany|Auenhausen]] with GM 406F\n***** Remote Radar Post 243 \"Silver Cork\", in [[Visselh\u00f6vede]] with GM 406F\n***** Remote Radar Post 244 \"Round up\", in [[Brockzetel]] with HADR\n***** Remote Radar Post 245 \"Bugle\", in [[Brekendorf]] with GM 406F\n*** Control and Reporting Training Inspection 23, in Erndtebr\u00fcck\n**** Education and Training Centre, in Erndtebr\u00fcck\n**** Education, Test and Training Group, in Erndtebr\u00fcck\n** Control and Reporting Centre 3 (Einsatzf\u00fchrungsbereich 3), in [[Sch\u00f6newalde]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Einsatzf\u00fchrungsbereich 3|url=http://www.luftwaffe.de/portal/a/luftwaffe/start/org/ruelog/efb3/!ut/p/z1/04_Sj9CPykssy0xPLMnMz0vMAfIjo8zinSx8QnyMLI2MfMIsXQw8DX29TS0tnTwDvQ30wwkpiAJKG-AAjgb6wSmp-pFAM8xxmOHo62uiH6wfpR-VlViWWKFXkF9UkpNaopeYDHKhfmRGYl5KTmpAfrIjRKAgN6LcoNxREQCur3jo/dz/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/#Z7_B8LTL2922LV9D0I1MK599BAMM4|publisher=German Air Force|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref>\n*** Operations Squadron 31, in Sch\u00f6newalde\n*** Operations Support Squadron 32, in Sch\u00f6newalde\n**** Sensor Platoon III, in [[C\u00f6lpin]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 351 \"Matchpoint\", in [[Putgarten]] with [[AN/FPS-117|RRP-117]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 352 \"Mindreader\", in C\u00f6lpin with RRP-117\n***** Remote Radar Post 353 \"Teddy Bear\", in [[Berlin Tempelhof Airport|Tempelhof]] with RRP-117\n***** Remote Radar Post 356 \"\", in [[Kalkhorst|Elmenhorst]] with RRP-117\n**** Sensor Platoon IV, in [[Regen]]\n***** Remote Radar Post 354 \"Blackmoor\", in [[D\u00f6bern]] with RRP-117\n***** Remote Radar Post 355 \"Royal Flash\", in [[Gleina]] with RRP-117\n***** Remote Radar Post 357 \"\", on [[D\u00f6braberg]] with RRP-117\n***** Remote Radar Post 358 \"Snow Cap\", on [[Gro\u00dfer Arber]] with RRP-117\n\n===Greece===\n\n1st Area Control Centre, inside Mount Chortiatis, with Marconi S-743D\n2nd Area Control Centre, inside Mount Parnitha, with Marconi S-743D\n9th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on Mount Pelion, with Marconi S-743D\n10th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on Mount Chortiatis, with Marconi S-743D\n\n{{Location map+ | Greece | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Didymoteicho]]</small>|lat=41.35|long=26.5|position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mount Ismaros|Ismaros]]</small>|lat=40.9|long=25.516667|position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mount Vitsi|Vitsi]]</small>|lat=40.649167|long=21.385556|position=right|mark=Brown 804000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Elati (mountain)|Elati]]</small>|lat=38.65|long=20.65|position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Kissamos]]</small>|lat=35.483333|long=23.65|position=left|mark=Brown 804000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mykonos]]</small>|lat=37.45|long=25.35|position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mount Mela|Mela]]</small>|lat=38.883333|long=24.516667|position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Lemnos]]</small>|lat=39.916667|long=25.25|position=right|mark=Blue pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mount Pelion|Pelion]]</small>|lat=39.438611|long=23.046389|position=right|mark=Brown 804000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=|lat=40.615|long=23.1|position=left|mark=Brown 804000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Ziros, Lasithi|Ziros]]</small>|lat=35.083333|long=26.133333|position=right|mark=Red ff0000 pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label='''[[Larissa National Airport|Larissa]]'''|lat=39.6491|long=22.465453|position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Mount Chortiatis|Chortiatis]]</small>|lat=40.583333|long=23.2|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Greece | background = white |label=<small>[[Parnitha]]</small>|lat=38.1734|long=23.7174|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n|caption=Hellenic Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] <br/> [[File:Red ff0000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]] <br/> [[File:Blue pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[BAE Systems|AR-327]] <br/> [[File:Brown 804000 pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Hellenic Air Force]]'s [[Combined Air Operations Centre]] (CAOC 7) at [[Larissa Air Base]] was deactivated in 2013 and its responsibilities transferred to the CAOC Torrej\u00f3n in Spain. The Hellenic Air Force fields two [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]], four [[BAE Systems|AR-327]] and six [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]] radar systems, however as of 2018 the air force is in the process of replacing some of its older systems with three [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] radars.\n\n* '''[[Hellenic Tactical Air Force Command|Air Force Tactical Command]]''', at [[Larissa Air Base]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Hellenic Air Force Tactical Command|url=https://www.haf.gr/structure/ata/|publisher=Hellenic Air Force|accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref>\n** Air Operations Centre, at Larissa Air Base<ref>{{cite web |url=http://koti.welho.com/msolanak/organogrengl.html |title=HAF organization |publisher=Koti.welho.com |accessdate=July 29, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829211030/http://koti.welho.com/msolanak/organogrengl.html |archivedate=August 29, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haf.gr/en/structure/units/ata/ |title=Hellenic Tactical Air Force |publisher=Haf.gr |date= |accessdate=July 29, 2009}}</ref>\n*** 1st Area Control Centre, inside [[Mount Chortiatis]]\n*** 2nd Area Control Centre, inside [[Mount Parnitha]]\n*** 1st Control and Warning Station Squadron, in [[Didymoteicho]], with [[BAE Systems|AR-327]]\n*** 2nd Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Mount Ismaros]], with [[Hughes HR-3000|HR-3000]]\n*** 3rd Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Mount Vitsi]], with [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]]\n*** 4th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Elati (mountain)|Mount Elati]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 5th Control and Warning Station Squadron, in [[Kissamos]], with [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]]\n*** 6th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Mykonos]], with AR-327\n*** 7th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Mount Mela]], with [[BAE Systems|AR-327]]\n*** 8th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Lemnos]], with AR-327\n*** 9th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on [[Mount Pelion]], with [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]]\n*** 10th Control and Warning Station Squadron, on Mount Chortiatis, with [[Marconi|Marconi S-743D]]\n*** 11th Control and Warning Station Squadron, in [[Ziros, Lasithi|Ziros]], with HR-3000\n\n=== Hungary ===\n{{Location map+ | Hungary | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Hungary | background = white |label='''[[Veszpr\u00e9m]]'''|lat= 47.09296 |long= 17.91377 |position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Hungary | background = white |label=<small>[[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]]</small>|lat= 46.679 |long= 20.4889 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Hungary | background = white |label=<small>[[B\u00e1nk\u00fat (Nagyvisny\u00f3)|B\u00e1nk\u00fat]]</small>|lat= 48.0989 |long= 21.091 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Hungary | background = white |label=<small>[[Medina, Hungary|Medina]]</small>|lat= 46.47363 |long= 18.64154 |position=right|mark=Blue 0080ff pog.svg}}\n|caption=Hungarian Air Force radar stations<br/>[[File:Blue 0080ff pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Command and Control Centre}}\n\nThe [[Hungarian Air Force]]'s Air Operations Centre is located in [[Veszpr\u00e9m]] and reports to CAOC Uedem. There are additional three radar companies with [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]-era equipment subordinate to the 54th Radar Regiment ''\"Veszpr\u00e9m\"'', however it is unclear if they will remain in service once Hungary's newest radar at [[Medina, Hungary|Medina]] reaches full operational capability.\n\n* '''Air Force Command''', in [[Budapest]]\n** Air Operations Centre, in [[Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n** 54th Radar Regiment ''\"Veszpr\u00e9m\"'', in Veszpr\u00e9m\n*** 1st Radar Data Centre, in [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]], with [[Selex RAT-31DL|RAT-31DL]]\n*** 2nd Radar Data Centre, in [[Medina, Hungary|Medina]], with RAT-31DL\n*** 3rd Radar Data Centre, in [[B\u00e1nk\u00fat (Nagyvisny\u00f3)|B\u00e1nk\u00fat]], with RAT-31DL\n\n=== Iceland ===\n{{Location map+ | Iceland | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Iceland | background = white |label='''[[Naval Air Station Keflavik|Keflavik]]'''|lat= 63.985 |long= -22.605556 |position=left|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Iceland | background = white |label=<small>[[Naval Air Station Keflavik|Mi\u00f0neshei\u00f0i]]</small>|lat= 63.985 |long= -22.45 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Iceland | background = white |label=<small>[[Langanes|Gunnolfsv\u00edk]]</small>|lat= 66.138056 |long= -15.105 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Iceland | background = white |label=<small>[[Stokksnes]]</small>|lat= 64.243 |long= -14.96 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Iceland | background = white |label=<small>[[Bolungarv\u00edk|Bolafjalli]]</small>|lat= 66.15 |long= -23.25 |position=right|mark=Orange pog.svg}}\n|caption=Iceland Air Defense System radar stations <br/> [[File:Orange pog.svg|8px]] Radar station with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(V)5]] <br/> [[File:Lightgreen pog.svg|8px]] Control and Reporting Centre}}\n\nThe [[Iceland Air Defence System|Iceland Air Defense System]], which is part of the [[Icelandic Coast Guard]], monitors [[Iceland]]'s airspace. Air Defense is provided by fighter jets from [[NATO]] allies, which rotate units for the [[Icelandic Air Policing]] mission to [[Naval Air Station Keflavik|Keflavik Air Base]].\nThe Iceland Air Defense System's Control and Reporting Centre is at Keflavik Air Base and reports to CAOC Uedem in Germany.\n\n* '''[[Iceland Air Defence System|Iceland Air Defense System]]''', at [[Naval Air Station Keflavik|Keflavik Air Base]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Iceland Air Defense System|url=http://www.lhg.is/varnarmal/loftrymisleit-og-islenska-loftvarnarkerfid|publisher=Icelandic Coast Guard|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n** Control and Reporting Centre, at Keflavik Air Base\n** H1 Radar Station, at [[Naval Air Station Keflavik|Mi\u00f0neshei\u00f0i]], with [[AN/FPS-117|AN/FPS-117(V)5]]\n** H2 Radar Station, on [[Langanes|Mount Gunnolfsv\u00edk]], with AN/FPS-117(V)5\n** H3 Radar Station, at [[Stokksnes]], with AN/FPS-117(V)5\n** H4 Radar Station, on [[Bolungarv\u00edk|Mount Bolafjalli]], with AN/FPS-117(V)5\n\n=== Italy ===\n{{Location map+ | Italy | relief = 1 | float=right | width=360| places=\n{{Location map~ | Italy | background = white |label='''[[Poggio Renatico|P. Renatico]]'''|lat=44.792876|long=11.494167|position=right|mark=Lightgreen pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ | Italy | background = white |label=<small>[[Poggio Ballone]]</small>|lat=42.829167|long=10.881111|po